1
00:00:09,118 --> 00:00:10,780
Oh, it's Tonfah?

2
00:00:11,063 --> 00:00:14,008
Yes. I study here, and I
happened to run into Phoon.

3
00:00:14,216 --> 00:00:16,400
Did Phoon mention Fun at all?

4
00:00:16,684 --> 00:00:17,927
Didn't I already tell you?

5
00:00:18,281 --> 00:00:20,293
You can study wherever you want,

6
00:00:20,474 --> 00:00:22,114
but don't get involved with Tonfah again.

7
00:00:22,154 --> 00:00:23,688
Is he hiding something from you?

8
00:00:24,182 --> 00:00:25,182
Maybe.

9
00:00:25,441 --> 00:00:28,908
I don't know… it's like if I make
even the slightest wrong move,

10
00:00:29,204 --> 00:00:30,560
I'll lose him forever.

11
00:00:30,706 --> 00:00:33,482
Are you sure he's just your brother?

12
00:00:33,831 --> 00:00:35,872
Phoon is P'Fah's important little brother.

13
00:00:36,288 --> 00:00:39,634
Do you even realize how
damn annoying you are, P'Fah?

14
00:00:43,902 --> 00:00:45,693
To Thorfun.

15
00:00:52,632 --> 00:00:53,934
In the end,

16
00:00:54,736 --> 00:00:57,448
Phoon chose to hurt the
person I loved the most,

17
00:00:57,690 --> 00:01:00,397
to protect someone else I loved.

18
00:01:01,174 --> 00:01:03,223
Now there's no P'Fah anymore.

19
00:01:03,882 --> 00:01:06,268
I hope Dad will love me a little more.

20
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:09,435
P'Fah asked if I hate him now.

21
00:01:10,362 --> 00:01:14,444
No way. Even if I died, I'd still love P'Fah.

22
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:17,358
The person I hate the most in the world

23
00:01:18,014 --> 00:01:19,306
is myself.

24
00:01:21,057 --> 00:01:24,139
A world without Fun and
P'Fah feels so hard to live in.

25
00:01:28,242 --> 00:01:30,210
But I already promised Fun.

26
00:01:31,789 --> 00:01:36,453
So I'll try to live well.
Please pray for me, Fun.

27
00:01:53,549 --> 00:01:54,585
Freshman?

28
00:01:54,946 --> 00:01:56,432
Yeah, freshman.

29
00:01:56,934 --> 00:01:58,106
Do we need to sign our names?

30
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,499
They told us to register here.

31
00:02:03,404 --> 00:02:05,398
Uh… I'm Easter.

32
00:02:05,672 --> 00:02:07,008
I'm Typhoon.

33
00:02:10,481 --> 00:02:11,481
I'll treat.

34
00:02:12,361 --> 00:02:13,365
Why?

35
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,280
Because you waited for me earlier.

36
00:02:16,373 --> 00:02:17,709
It's really okay, though.

37
00:02:18,890 --> 00:02:20,915
- Try it.
- So who are we waiting for?

38
00:02:22,428 --> 00:02:23,558
My roommate.

39
00:02:25,121 --> 00:02:26,505
Where the hell is he?

40
00:02:27,706 --> 00:02:28,706
Why isn't he here yet?

41
00:02:48,909 --> 00:02:50,474
Man, speak of the devil. Hurry up.

42
00:02:59,367 --> 00:03:00,367
Phoon.

43
00:03:00,894 --> 00:03:02,605
This is my roommate, North.

44
00:03:03,617 --> 00:03:06,091
♪♪♪North—this is Phoon, my friend.

45
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:07,771
Wow, so I'm “♪♪♪North” now?

46
00:03:07,897 --> 00:03:09,293
Yeah, suits you perfectly.

47
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,854
- Did you order mine not sweet?
- I did.

48
00:03:12,682 --> 00:03:14,607
I ordered it extra sweet.

49
00:03:15,471 --> 00:03:16,600
I don't like it.

50
00:03:17,143 --> 00:03:17,970
Well, I do.

51
00:03:18,165 --> 00:03:20,565
- If you like it, eat it yourself.
- Fine, but you're paying.

52
00:03:21,354 --> 00:03:22,102
Again?

53
00:03:22,185 --> 00:03:24,185
Phoon, don't go hanging
out with people like this.

54
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:27,168
I'm North, first-year
electrical engineering.

55
00:03:27,445 --> 00:03:29,804
I'm Typhoon, first-year veterinary.

56
00:03:31,077 --> 00:03:33,031
- Where are you from?
- Phuket.

57
00:03:33,228 --> 00:03:35,432
Seriously?

58
00:03:35,631 --> 00:03:39,013
Can you speak Southern Thai?

59
00:03:39,484 --> 00:03:41,330
- I can't.
- Oh, you can't?

60
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:43,374
- What about you, North?
- I'm from Lampang.

61
00:03:43,554 --> 00:03:48,245
But I'm not very good at it yet. I still
need to learn. I'll teach you later, okay?

62
00:03:49,078 --> 00:03:49,866
Got it?

63
00:03:49,934 --> 00:03:51,854
Translate it. Put subtitles up now.

64
00:03:52,008 --> 00:03:53,456
Make them big. I'm confused.

65
00:03:56,211 --> 00:03:58,312
Au means speaking. Bo-Chang
means you're not good at it.

66
00:03:58,336 --> 00:04:01,112
Life in university isn't
as bad as I thought.

67
00:04:01,634 --> 00:04:03,377
I think I'm doing pretty well.

68
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:06,291
Fun, you don't have to worry.

69
00:04:09,691 --> 00:04:11,506
I met really good friends.

70
00:04:12,035 --> 00:04:13,712
So good that I wonder

71
00:04:13,997 --> 00:04:15,597
if someone like me really deserves them.

72
00:04:18,485 --> 00:04:21,074
Didn't you say turn left? I followed you!

73
00:04:21,327 --> 00:04:23,031
Well, that is left.

74
00:04:23,752 --> 00:04:24,752
That's right.

75
00:04:24,928 --> 00:04:28,111
But sometimes fate likes to play tricks.

76
00:04:28,395 --> 00:04:29,395
Sorry.

77
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:30,860
Whatever.

78
00:04:31,518 --> 00:04:34,010
Ter said someone would
come pick us up, right?

79
00:04:34,342 --> 00:04:35,342
So we'll...

80
00:04:36,982 --> 00:04:40,583
- Let's wait around here.
- Because no matter how far I get lost,

81
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,573
You're Ter's friend, right?

82
00:04:51,471 --> 00:04:53,619
P'Fah will always find me.

83
00:05:06,303 --> 00:05:07,550
P'Hill.

84
00:05:07,629 --> 00:05:08,629
Snacks.

85
00:05:09,096 --> 00:05:11,629
- Hi, Easter.
- Hi.

86
00:05:13,431 --> 00:05:14,594
Here's a sandwich.

87
00:05:21,505 --> 00:05:23,022
- Want some?
- Yeah, sure.

88
00:07:03,216 --> 00:07:05,694
That's it for today. You can all go home.

89
00:07:06,549 --> 00:07:08,626
Yay! Let's go!

90
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:11,890
Hey.

91
00:07:12,703 --> 00:07:14,017
Let's go reading today.

92
00:07:14,604 --> 00:07:15,637
So diligent.

93
00:07:15,899 --> 00:07:17,648
Of course.

94
00:07:18,005 --> 00:07:21,539
P'Mhor are always studying,
and I also want to see P'Hill.

95
00:07:22,699 --> 00:07:26,312
That's called wanting to see your
boyfriend, not studying. Don't make excuses.

96
00:07:28,854 --> 00:07:33,481
Here, Phoon. You want to take the
med exam, right? Got P'Mhor to tutor you.

97
00:07:33,642 --> 00:07:35,139
Come on, please.

98
00:07:35,915 --> 00:07:38,582
Even though deep down
I don't want you to pass.

99
00:07:39,595 --> 00:07:41,525
Look at him, cursing his own friend.

100
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:42,961
Hey, I'm not cursing anyone.

101
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,875
What, you want me to stay alone
with you in the faculty or something?

102
00:07:44,899 --> 00:07:48,419
- What's wrong with being with me?
- See? This is exactly what happens when I'm with you.

103
00:07:48,918 --> 00:07:50,717
Phoon, look at your friend.

104
00:07:52,644 --> 00:07:54,120
I'm gonna miss you.

105
00:07:54,638 --> 00:07:55,773
Come on, let's go.

106
00:07:56,792 --> 00:07:57,297
Mm.

107
00:07:57,487 --> 00:07:59,727
Ugh, you're overthinking it
like it's an exam. Let's go.

108
00:08:00,087 --> 00:08:04,008
- Fine, I'll go too.
- That's right, Foam. If Phoon's going, you have to go too.

109
00:08:05,038 --> 00:08:06,911
I can't. I've got plans today.

110
00:08:07,383 --> 00:08:08,139
With who?

111
00:08:08,398 --> 00:08:10,143
I'm allowed to have plans
sometimes, you know.

112
00:08:10,167 --> 00:08:12,111
You've got plans every day.

113
00:08:12,337 --> 00:08:15,733
Just remember this—let your
girlfriend help you during exams then.

114
00:08:15,797 --> 00:08:16,939
Ugh, stop nagging.

115
00:08:17,765 --> 00:08:19,829
Hurry up, Phoon.

116
00:08:20,401 --> 00:08:21,721
Our gang only has two people now.

117
00:08:45,229 --> 00:08:46,745
Huh? Where's everyone else?

118
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:50,211
Probably buying snacks.

119
00:08:50,819 --> 00:08:53,216
- They're on their way.
- Oh.

120
00:09:01,851 --> 00:09:03,257
You sleep your life away.

121
00:09:03,351 --> 00:09:04,681
And eating my space too.

122
00:09:09,419 --> 00:09:10,768
That's just how it is.

123
00:09:14,884 --> 00:09:16,506
Maybe… this is for the best.

124
00:09:29,848 --> 00:09:31,334
Auntie Nuan.

125
00:09:38,503 --> 00:09:39,774
Yes, Auntie Nuan.

126
00:09:39,909 --> 00:09:41,863
How have you been, Phoon?

127
00:09:42,669 --> 00:09:43,754
I'm doing well.

128
00:09:44,112 --> 00:09:45,669
And you, Auntie Nuan?

129
00:09:45,884 --> 00:09:49,859
I'm fine. Why haven't
you contacted me at all?

130
00:09:50,137 --> 00:09:54,229
I'm sorry, Auntie. I've
been really busy lately.

131
00:09:54,659 --> 00:09:58,260
Phoon, have you heard?
The house has been sold.

132
00:10:00,623 --> 00:10:02,762
- Really?
- Yes.

133
00:10:03,084 --> 00:10:06,539
Today the Mister asked me to
come pack things up for the last time.

134
00:10:06,761 --> 00:10:10,641
There are still some of your things left, Phoon.
I just couldn't bring myself to throw them away.

135
00:10:11,044 --> 00:10:12,891
Will you come back to the house?

136
00:10:17,542 --> 00:10:18,542
Yes.

137
00:10:19,045 --> 00:10:20,998
I still have some free days next week.

138
00:10:21,317 --> 00:10:24,653
Alright then. Call me when you arrive.

139
00:10:24,902 --> 00:10:26,189
I'll be waiting.

140
00:10:26,705 --> 00:10:27,705
Okay.

141
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,180
Fun.

142
00:10:42,164 --> 00:10:44,351
Another piece of proof of
the memories we shared…

143
00:10:45,082 --> 00:10:46,844
Is about to disappear.

144
00:11:11,494 --> 00:11:14,047
So what will you do next, Auntie Nuan?

145
00:11:14,194 --> 00:11:16,514
I'll probably go back home
and take care of my grandchild.

146
00:11:17,042 --> 00:11:18,471
I'm getting old already.

147
00:11:19,051 --> 00:11:21,328
I don't think I'll look for another job.

148
00:11:22,084 --> 00:11:24,974
That's good. You'll finally get some rest.

149
00:11:25,514 --> 00:11:28,688
You raised me and Fun for so many years.

150
00:11:31,002 --> 00:11:34,401
Shall we go see Fun first?

151
00:11:34,835 --> 00:11:35,835
Yes.

152
00:11:48,278 --> 00:11:49,429
Auntie Nuan…

153
00:11:50,524 --> 00:11:53,986
Is it possible… that Fun is still here?

154
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:56,957
Phoon

155
00:11:57,927 --> 00:12:00,077
I don't want to say this, but

156
00:12:01,017 --> 00:12:02,017
still…

157
00:12:02,171 --> 00:12:05,493
Those who have passed on are gone.

158
00:12:06,842 --> 00:12:10,524
If you keep holding
on, it will only hurt more.

159
00:12:13,711 --> 00:12:17,425
Fun wouldn't want you to be in pain either.

160
00:12:31,654 --> 00:12:32,814
Fun…

161
00:12:33,805 --> 00:12:35,500
Auntie misses you.

162
00:12:52,296 --> 00:12:53,665
I'm back.

163
00:12:56,213 --> 00:12:57,287
Did you miss me?

164
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,133
I'm sorry that I…

165
00:13:00,491 --> 00:13:02,608
Couldn't come see you
every day like before.

166
00:13:05,414 --> 00:13:06,672
You must've been so lonely.

167
00:13:13,545 --> 00:13:15,066
I dream about you too, Fun.

168
00:13:16,114 --> 00:13:18,925
In my dreams, it feels so real…

169
00:13:20,042 --> 00:13:21,853
Sometimes I think…

170
00:13:23,032 --> 00:13:24,771
You'll really come see me.

171
00:13:29,494 --> 00:13:31,001
I'm sorry for being selfish.

172
00:13:33,391 --> 00:13:34,709
Would you be mad at me, Fun,

173
00:13:35,271 --> 00:13:36,954
if I wished you could stay?

174
00:13:40,192 --> 00:13:41,752
I don't want you to go anywhere at all.

175
00:14:20,198 --> 00:14:22,339
These are all that's left of Fun's things.

176
00:14:22,642 --> 00:14:23,942
What should we do?

177
00:14:28,733 --> 00:14:30,318
Can we donate them?

178
00:14:31,111 --> 00:14:32,265
Would that be okay?

179
00:14:32,903 --> 00:14:34,124
I think…

180
00:14:34,911 --> 00:14:37,702
Fun would want them to be useful to others.

181
00:14:39,871 --> 00:14:42,167
I'm not sure if I should say this,

182
00:14:43,105 --> 00:14:44,592
but there's something.

183
00:14:45,204 --> 00:14:46,992
I want you to know.

184
00:14:48,694 --> 00:14:49,840
What is it?

185
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:53,751
Fun knew from the very beginning

186
00:14:54,062 --> 00:14:56,776
that you weren't the
biological child of this family.

187
00:15:00,727 --> 00:15:01,727
Really?

188
00:15:04,038 --> 00:15:09,560
That night, Fun and I overheard
Miss and Mister arguing.

189
00:15:11,545 --> 00:15:15,662
I was afraid Fun might not take it well,

190
00:15:17,134 --> 00:15:18,595
but it turned out that…

191
00:15:19,158 --> 00:15:20,440
Fun…

192
00:15:20,835 --> 00:15:22,878
Still loved you just the same.

193
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,567
But after Fun passed away,

194
00:15:29,054 --> 00:15:31,133
everything started to fall apart.

195
00:15:32,037 --> 00:15:34,940
I didn't know what to do either.

196
00:15:38,205 --> 00:15:41,444
Phoon, you're not the one
who destroyed this family.

197
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:45,120
Fun never thought that way.

198
00:15:47,521 --> 00:15:49,296
Please don't blame yourself.

199
00:15:56,451 --> 00:15:57,531
Thank you.

200
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:46,278
The truth I wanted you
to come see… is all of this.

201
00:16:47,293 --> 00:16:49,958
Mister wanted me to throw these away.

202
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,623
But I secretly kept them.

203
00:16:54,927 --> 00:16:56,237
What are they?

204
00:16:59,470 --> 00:17:03,348
They've been sent since
you were one year old, Phoon.

205
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:05,631
Every year.

206
00:17:06,087 --> 00:17:07,524
Around March.

207
00:17:08,647 --> 00:17:10,247
Your birth month.

208
00:17:11,927 --> 00:17:14,303
There's no sender's name, but…

209
00:17:14,774 --> 00:17:15,927
There is a recipient's name.

210
00:17:20,613 --> 00:17:21,613
My mom?

211
00:17:24,757 --> 00:17:28,740
Miss threw away many of them already.

212
00:17:29,047 --> 00:17:32,588
This is all I could secretly keep.

213
00:17:38,548 --> 00:17:39,656
It's okay.

214
00:17:40,398 --> 00:17:41,600
This is already enough.

215
00:17:42,814 --> 00:17:44,280
Thank you, Auntie Nuan.

216
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:51,102
I hope things are the
way you think they are.

217
00:17:52,074 --> 00:17:55,484
At least your real
mother still thinks of you.

218
00:17:56,508 --> 00:17:59,742
But she must have had some reason…

219
00:18:00,023 --> 00:18:02,002
That kept her from coming to see you.

220
00:18:06,028 --> 00:18:07,028
Yes.

221
00:18:07,739 --> 00:18:09,456
I hope she had a reason.

222
00:18:10,574 --> 00:18:12,100
Any reason at all.

223
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,220
As long as it wasn't
because she didn't love me.

224
00:19:06,573 --> 00:19:08,913
Back from Phuket yet?

225
00:19:08,937 --> 00:19:10,691
Yeah, just got back to my room.

226
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,300
We're having a dinner party.

227
00:19:13,328 --> 00:19:14,850
What's the occasion?

228
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:17,423
The occasion is that we feel like eating.

229
00:19:19,124 --> 00:19:21,078
Who's going?

230
00:19:21,490 --> 00:19:24,266
Me, North, P'Hill, and P'Hill's friends.

231
00:19:28,164 --> 00:19:29,343
P'Hill's friends?

232
00:19:29,724 --> 00:19:32,422
Yeah, lots of people. It'll be fun.

233
00:19:38,481 --> 00:19:39,481
But…

234
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,722
Alright, I'll go.

235
00:19:46,216 --> 00:19:47,970
Cool. I'll pick you up.

236
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:50,001
Mm, okay.

237
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:00,145
So are you going or not?

238
00:20:00,777 --> 00:20:02,056
I think I won't go.

239
00:20:02,597 --> 00:20:03,694
Because of Phoon?

240
00:20:06,188 --> 00:20:07,188
Yeah.

241
00:20:08,042 --> 00:20:10,082
He'd probably feel more
comfortable if I didn't go.

242
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:13,844
You should talk it out
already. It's awkward.

243
00:20:14,682 --> 00:20:16,330
Does he even want to talk to me?

244
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:21,668
He can't even look at my face.

245
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:27,595
Okay, I'll stop. You get like
this every time Phoon comes up.

246
00:20:27,877 --> 00:20:29,764
I'll tell them you're busy.

247
00:20:30,269 --> 00:20:31,269
Mm.

248
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:45,871
P'Fah, look. The sky's so beautiful today.

249
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:48,311
Even though it rained so hard last night.

250
00:20:49,573 --> 00:20:53,198
It's nice that the sky can
make you smile this much.

251
00:21:15,231 --> 00:21:16,231
Hey!

252
00:21:16,694 --> 00:21:17,934
So where the hell did Fah go?

253
00:21:18,262 --> 00:21:19,262
He's busy.

254
00:21:19,545 --> 00:21:20,688
What do you mean, busy?

255
00:21:21,007 --> 00:21:23,730
Why are you asking so many
questions? Busy means busy.

256
00:21:23,754 --> 00:21:25,118
You're annoying as hell.

257
00:21:25,238 --> 00:21:27,231
Damn it, Jo, I only said two sentences.

258
00:21:27,574 --> 00:21:29,271
- Asshole.
- Asshole?

259
00:21:29,414 --> 00:21:30,515
What kind of asshole?

260
00:21:31,085 --> 00:21:32,365
Hill, look at him picking on me.

261
00:21:38,149 --> 00:21:40,001
Hey, didn't you say you were busy?

262
00:21:48,441 --> 00:21:51,201
The more I think about it, the
more I feel like being free is better.

263
00:21:52,619 --> 00:21:54,259
What do you mean, “being free is better”?

264
00:21:56,946 --> 00:22:00,198
Arthit, I want to sit here.

265
00:22:02,797 --> 00:22:05,951
The hell's wrong with you? There's
tons of space—go sit somewhere else.

266
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:08,090
Go sit next to Jo. Your fling.

267
00:22:09,151 --> 00:22:10,179
Jo? My fling?

268
00:22:10,311 --> 00:22:11,311
Yeah.

269
00:22:11,804 --> 00:22:12,804
This asshole?

270
00:22:12,909 --> 00:22:14,408
Come on, hurry up.

271
00:22:15,949 --> 00:22:17,397
I'm doing this just for you.

272
00:22:18,431 --> 00:22:19,685
I don't even want to sit there.

273
00:22:20,234 --> 00:22:21,234
Next to that poser.

274
00:22:29,260 --> 00:22:30,460
Want to move to another table?

275
00:22:35,124 --> 00:22:36,124
Hey.

276
00:22:37,656 --> 00:22:39,100
Long time no see.

277
00:22:45,059 --> 00:22:46,059
Yeah.

278
00:22:58,223 --> 00:22:59,456
Phoon, want some shrimp?

279
00:23:00,801 --> 00:23:02,041
- Huh?
- Careful, it's dripping.

280
00:23:02,395 --> 00:23:03,817
Looks damn good. Share some with me.

281
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:05,116
- Share what?
- The shrimp.

282
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:07,112
- What shrimp?
- The one you're peeling right now.

283
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:08,654
If you want shrimp, order your own.

284
00:23:08,684 --> 00:23:10,647
Wow, North, you've got some nerve.

285
00:23:10,758 --> 00:23:13,155
I never once complained about
you eating my stuff from the fridge.

286
00:23:13,179 --> 00:23:14,634
- Stuff from the fridge?
- Yeah.

287
00:23:15,653 --> 00:23:18,417
Weren't you buying it to share?

288
00:23:19,540 --> 00:23:20,540
To share?

289
00:23:20,841 --> 00:23:21,780
- Share with you?
- Yeah.

290
00:23:21,804 --> 00:23:24,561
- You're the one stealing.
- Then just tell me next time.

291
00:23:24,625 --> 00:23:26,389
Basic manners say you should ask first.

292
00:23:26,602 --> 00:23:27,922
Since when do I have manners?

293
00:23:27,992 --> 00:23:29,355
- You don't.
- Exactly.

294
00:23:29,379 --> 00:23:30,845
- Give it to me.
- Don't eat it.

295
00:23:31,008 --> 00:23:32,487
Two pieces. Peel them too.

296
00:23:33,508 --> 00:23:34,508
Always me.

297
00:23:34,542 --> 00:23:35,641
Good job.

298
00:23:37,690 --> 00:23:39,342
Hey, peel it properly.

299
00:23:45,902 --> 00:23:47,309
Shrimp. It's shrimp. Keep it neat.

300
00:23:49,903 --> 00:23:50,936
Thank you.

301
00:24:06,462 --> 00:24:09,503
Hey, why are they taking so long to pay?

302
00:24:09,804 --> 00:24:10,804
Yeah, seriously.

303
00:24:11,822 --> 00:24:15,266
Or are P'Mhor arguing over who should pay?

304
00:24:16,309 --> 00:24:18,509
One thing's for sure—P'Arthit
won't be one of them.

305
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:23,927
Phoon.

306
00:24:24,219 --> 00:24:25,219
Hm?

307
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:29,136
I've got something I want to ask you.

308
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:35,438
Jeez, you're stalling again.
When are you gonna ask?

309
00:24:35,546 --> 00:24:36,546
I'll ask.

310
00:24:36,739 --> 00:24:38,699
- So what's going on between you and P'Fah?
- Huh?

311
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:41,986
Damn it, North. You really
don't beat around the bush.

312
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,768
Who would even know how to answer that?

313
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,434
You keep going “uh… uh…” like that.

314
00:24:48,442 --> 00:24:51,026
It's a long story.

315
00:24:51,285 --> 00:24:52,905
Are you guys ready to hear it?

316
00:24:53,259 --> 00:24:55,271
Ready. Totally ready.

317
00:24:56,288 --> 00:24:57,734
Yeah, go on.

318
00:25:01,946 --> 00:25:02,946
So…

319
00:25:04,718 --> 00:25:05,868
So?

320
00:25:06,368 --> 00:25:08,518
Me and P'Fah…

321
00:25:08,663 --> 00:25:10,222
Yeah? What about it?

322
00:25:11,122 --> 00:25:12,402
What are you guys talking about?

323
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:15,040
Oh—nothing, P'Hill.

324
00:25:15,238 --> 00:25:16,505
I'm so full. Let's head back.

325
00:25:16,577 --> 00:25:18,488
Bye, P'. Bye.

326
00:25:18,574 --> 00:25:19,998
Bye, P'Hill.

327
00:25:20,259 --> 00:25:21,491
See you.

328
00:25:22,474 --> 00:25:23,998
What were you guys talking about?

329
00:25:25,231 --> 00:25:28,068
Hmm… top-level secret.

330
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:30,365
If you want to know,
transfer some money first.

331
00:25:31,211 --> 00:25:32,211
Go get it at home.

332
00:25:35,789 --> 00:25:37,002
I'm heading off.

333
00:25:37,034 --> 00:25:38,324
P'Jo, have you transferred yet?

334
00:25:38,368 --> 00:25:40,754
- I'm coming with you, Jo.
- Why are you coming?

335
00:26:29,115 --> 00:26:30,539
Dao? How did you get here?

336
00:26:30,586 --> 00:26:32,991
Ta-da!

337
00:26:33,226 --> 00:26:34,302
I called him myself.

338
00:26:34,619 --> 00:26:39,717
I felt like the problem you're dealing with is
too big for just me and North to handle alone.

339
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:43,287
Don't tell me everyone
showing up this morning

340
00:26:43,783 --> 00:26:45,703
was because of me and P'Fah?

341
00:26:45,832 --> 00:26:46,832
Yeah.

342
00:26:48,506 --> 00:26:50,586
So how long are you gonna
make me wait? Come inside.

343
00:26:51,377 --> 00:26:53,946
- Fine.
- Go on in, Dao. Don't be shy.

344
00:26:54,656 --> 00:26:56,216
Hey, aren't you gonna grab some snacks?

345
00:26:57,099 --> 00:26:58,285
Come on, I'm starving.

346
00:26:59,256 --> 00:27:01,127
Alright, you guys. Start talking.

347
00:27:01,268 --> 00:27:03,819
Today, no need to wait
for Foam. He chose sleep.

348
00:27:04,054 --> 00:27:06,970
Think about it—between friends
and sleep, he chose sleep.

349
00:27:07,186 --> 00:27:09,822
And you? Between friends
and food, what do you choose?

350
00:27:10,128 --> 00:27:13,395
- I choose 'between'
- Choose what? Be clear.

351
00:27:13,955 --> 00:27:14,955
I choose everything.

352
00:27:16,531 --> 00:27:17,871
I'll give you one more chance.

353
00:27:18,342 --> 00:27:20,395
Fine—eating with friends.

354
00:27:21,620 --> 00:27:22,717
You're such a glutton.

355
00:27:22,764 --> 00:27:24,103
Come on, North.

356
00:27:25,580 --> 00:27:26,645
Aren't you gonna eat?

357
00:27:31,555 --> 00:27:33,271
Alright, let's do this.

358
00:27:35,115 --> 00:27:36,971
The reason we're all here today...

359
00:27:37,071 --> 00:27:38,071
Mm.

360
00:27:38,405 --> 00:27:39,435
So what is it, exactly?

361
00:27:42,071 --> 00:27:43,071
It's about me.

362
00:27:46,517 --> 00:27:49,900
Yeah, I know it's about
you—but can you actually tell us?

363
00:27:50,598 --> 00:27:51,754
It's about me.

364
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:54,592
My story.

365
00:27:54,807 --> 00:27:56,685
Fine, then. I won't pry.

366
00:27:58,205 --> 00:28:00,216
I just don't know how to explain it—like...

367
00:28:00,437 --> 00:28:01,668
Relax, Maew. Just kidding.

368
00:28:02,266 --> 00:28:03,266
So what is it?

369
00:28:04,217 --> 00:28:05,217
Can you tell us?

370
00:28:06,075 --> 00:28:07,075
Is it a secret?

371
00:28:09,465 --> 00:28:10,604
A big secret?

372
00:28:11,755 --> 00:28:13,192
A really big one.

373
00:28:14,014 --> 00:28:15,674
I don't want anyone to know.

374
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,162
Especially...

375
00:28:17,804 --> 00:28:18,804
P'Mhor.

376
00:28:23,105 --> 00:28:24,315
But I have one request.

377
00:28:24,951 --> 00:28:26,065
After I tell you

378
00:28:26,894 --> 00:28:28,638
don't hate me, okay?

379
00:28:30,780 --> 00:28:32,151
We don't hate you.

380
00:28:32,696 --> 00:28:34,943
Even if you will scratch
us, we won't hate it.

381
00:28:36,114 --> 00:28:37,659
You said it yourself—remember that.

382
00:28:37,882 --> 00:28:39,642
In case one day you
feel like scratching us.

383
00:28:39,914 --> 00:28:42,260
Yeah, no one's gonna hate you.

384
00:28:43,481 --> 00:28:45,591
- You can relax.
- Then...

385
00:28:46,567 --> 00:28:49,044
- Start talking.
- Yeah, go on.

386
00:29:14,971 --> 00:29:17,960
So that's why you like taking
pictures of the sky, right?

387
00:29:21,317 --> 00:29:22,826
Because you like P'Fah.

388
00:29:24,794 --> 00:29:26,678
Honestly, after hearing everything

389
00:29:27,117 --> 00:29:31,506
what the hell is wrong with your dad?

390
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:34,186
It makes me so mad just listening to it.

391
00:29:36,602 --> 00:29:38,475
Thanks for getting angry on my behalf.

392
00:29:38,736 --> 00:29:40,531
Yeah… not everyone

393
00:29:41,191 --> 00:29:42,882
is ready to be a parent.

394
00:29:43,564 --> 00:29:44,564
But still

395
00:29:44,961 --> 00:29:46,805
he's already my dad.

396
00:29:47,997 --> 00:29:50,543
And he's the only one I have left.

397
00:29:52,561 --> 00:29:55,331
Yeah… you're really strong.

398
00:29:56,985 --> 00:29:58,792
- Me?
- Yeah.

399
00:29:59,219 --> 00:30:01,306
After all that, you can still smile.

400
00:30:01,811 --> 00:30:03,158
You're seriously amazing.

401
00:30:05,860 --> 00:30:06,860
Ah.

402
00:30:07,026 --> 00:30:10,259
Hey, it's okay. Come on, group hug.

403
00:30:12,071 --> 00:30:13,980
- Ouch!
- I'm joining too.

404
00:30:17,650 --> 00:30:18,925
Thanks, everyone.

405
00:30:23,442 --> 00:30:25,284
Alright, alright.

406
00:30:27,703 --> 00:30:28,903
So… who's comforting who here?

407
00:30:29,214 --> 00:30:30,512
It's just sad, okay?

408
00:30:30,591 --> 00:30:32,905
Come on, it's not even your story.

409
00:30:40,023 --> 00:30:41,023
It's okay.

410
00:30:45,285 --> 00:30:46,484
Is that P'Fun?

411
00:30:48,339 --> 00:30:49,339
Yeah.

412
00:30:54,331 --> 00:30:55,851
You still keep the photo up like this.

413
00:30:56,435 --> 00:30:57,742
Don't you miss her like crazy?

414
00:30:58,585 --> 00:30:59,851
I miss her a lot.

415
00:31:01,139 --> 00:31:02,911
My tear is back—pause it first.

416
00:31:05,728 --> 00:31:06,728
Hey!

417
00:31:06,856 --> 00:31:08,331
I've got a great idea for you.

418
00:31:12,028 --> 00:31:13,168
Here.

419
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:18,509
Here.

420
00:31:19,226 --> 00:31:20,426
Why don't we put our photo up?

421
00:31:21,342 --> 00:31:22,490
Isn't that a bad idea?

422
00:31:27,585 --> 00:31:30,305
Here—right here. You're the guardian
spirit, so you belong down here.

423
00:31:30,474 --> 00:31:32,180
Ah—hey!

424
00:31:35,367 --> 00:31:37,247
So I have to study while
staring at your faces?

425
00:31:37,391 --> 00:31:38,816
- Exactly.
- Yep.

426
00:31:39,001 --> 00:31:40,536
Like we're keeping you company.

427
00:31:41,444 --> 00:31:42,466
That's nice.

428
00:31:42,502 --> 00:31:44,595
He kind of like it.

429
00:31:44,715 --> 00:31:46,475
- Don't ask me for more, though.
- Yea.

430
00:31:46,792 --> 00:31:47,792
That's all I've got.

431
00:31:48,228 --> 00:31:49,228
Just one photo.

432
00:31:54,693 --> 00:31:57,082
So what are you gonna do about P'Fah?

433
00:31:59,032 --> 00:32:00,259
I honestly don't know yet.

434
00:32:01,333 --> 00:32:03,598
Are you just gonna let
things stay awkward like this?

435
00:32:04,404 --> 00:32:05,782
It's just…

436
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:07,204
Not a good idea.

437
00:32:07,804 --> 00:32:09,125
It's way too awkward.

438
00:32:09,822 --> 00:32:11,842
Yeah, I noticed.

439
00:32:12,048 --> 00:32:13,402
I think you and P'Fah are

440
00:32:13,607 --> 00:32:16,245
- weird.
- Do you think P'Fah's mad at me, North?

441
00:32:16,450 --> 00:32:17,851
For pushing him away like that?

442
00:32:19,068 --> 00:32:20,190
If it were me?

443
00:32:20,908 --> 00:32:22,087
I'd punch you.

444
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:26,277
- That bad?
- That bad. With a mouth like that, you deserve it.

445
00:32:26,327 --> 00:32:27,777
Then you'd be first in line.

446
00:32:29,125 --> 00:32:31,828
- I probably do deserve a punch.
- Yeah, bring your face here.

447
00:32:33,482 --> 00:32:35,977
- Say no more.
- Hey, what are you doing?

448
00:32:36,242 --> 00:32:38,829
He wants to get punched, is that okay?

449
00:32:38,830 --> 00:32:48,962
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

450
00:32:38,887 --> 00:32:40,657
You scare him. Come here.

451
00:32:46,430 --> 00:32:48,080
I've been thinking about this all along.

452
00:32:48,850 --> 00:32:50,630
That I could get over P'Fah.

453
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,250
If I just stayed out of it, it should end.

454
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:56,080
But the more we see each other,

455
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:57,950
the more distant we feel.

456
00:33:01,650 --> 00:33:02,990
I guess I just regret it.

457
00:33:03,030 --> 00:33:04,910
That things can't go back to how they were.

458
00:33:06,650 --> 00:33:08,260
And it hurts.

459
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:11,470
If in the end, I have to lose P'Fah.

460
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,910
So what was “before” like, then?

461
00:33:17,380 --> 00:33:18,380
Well…

462
00:33:18,510 --> 00:33:20,120
We took care of each other.

463
00:33:20,460 --> 00:33:22,740
We worried about each other. We meant well.

464
00:33:24,050 --> 00:33:25,660
I just want him to know that

465
00:33:26,310 --> 00:33:27,760
if he has no one,

466
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,670
and he turns around,

467
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,720
he'll always find me right here.

468
00:33:34,250 --> 00:33:36,250
No matter who I am in his life.

469
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:41,460
No matter who you are in his life?

470
00:33:48,610 --> 00:33:49,670
I've got it.

471
00:33:50,540 --> 00:33:53,010
A way for Maew to talk to P'Fah,

472
00:33:53,300 --> 00:33:54,580
to look after him,

473
00:33:54,970 --> 00:33:57,870
and let P'Fah know someone always cares.

474
00:34:01,260 --> 00:34:02,260
What is it?

475
00:34:08,030 --> 00:34:09,030
He's here.

476
00:34:10,030 --> 00:34:11,710
Hey!

477
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:18,200
Let's see—what was the
first thing you gave P'Fah?

478
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:20,170
- What is it?
- A sandwich and chocolate milk.

479
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:22,480
Isn't that too basic?

480
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:25,790
I didn't know what he
liked, so I bought what I like.

481
00:34:26,750 --> 00:34:28,650
But I think P'Fah would like it.

482
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,830
Hey, I already re-check with P'Hill.

483
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:34,040
You can take the stuff

484
00:34:34,230 --> 00:34:35,490
and leave it before class.

485
00:34:35,830 --> 00:34:36,830
Mm.

486
00:34:37,940 --> 00:34:39,600
Have you written him a letter yet?

487
00:34:40,050 --> 00:34:40,780
I have.

488
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:42,260
See? A smiling picture.

489
00:34:45,610 --> 00:34:47,690
Even with zero expectations,
I'm still disappointed.

490
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:51,070
Why didn't you write at least a message?
So he'd know how you feel.

491
00:34:52,460 --> 00:34:55,730
It's my first one. I didn't
know what to write.

492
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,740
Um… Hello.

493
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,440
That's way too basic.

494
00:35:00,830 --> 00:35:04,600
You've gotta write more than that,
so he'll remember you.

495
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:07,160
P'Fah, I freaking like you so much.

496
00:35:07,420 --> 00:35:09,080
Hey, that works!

497
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,330
I'm kidding.

498
00:35:10,630 --> 00:35:11,630
Ugh.

499
00:35:11,930 --> 00:35:13,080
But we agree, though.

500
00:35:13,390 --> 00:35:16,080
We think he'd find it kind of funny.

501
00:35:17,860 --> 00:35:20,040
Yeah, just write it. Trust me.

502
00:35:21,490 --> 00:35:22,850
Okay.

503
00:35:24,110 --> 00:35:26,930
Come on, you practiced forging
handwriting, right? Let me see.

504
00:35:28,150 --> 00:35:29,560
I

505
00:35:29,820 --> 00:35:31,090
Really like P'.

506
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:32,460
So much.

507
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:37,900
But if you call him “P',” won't
he know we're freshmen?

508
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:39,170
Yeah.

509
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:45,110
I think you should write “you.”

510
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,246
That way he won't know
if it's a senior or a junior.

511
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:47,810
Right?

512
00:35:48,050 --> 00:35:49,960
- “You?”
- Yeah, write “you.” Better that way.

513
00:35:50,090 --> 00:35:51,690
Smart for once.

514
00:35:51,970 --> 00:35:53,190
In my whole life.

515
00:35:54,350 --> 00:35:57,130
I really, really like you.

516
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:58,910
So much.

517
00:35:59,040 --> 00:36:00,910
- Yeah.
- That's it. Exactly.

518
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:02,290
Let's do this.

519
00:36:03,930 --> 00:36:05,500
Let's go. Let's go.

520
00:36:06,340 --> 00:36:09,780
Do you think this method will really work?

521
00:36:10,010 --> 00:36:13,550
You're already this far.
You can't back out now.

522
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:16,400
Or if Maew's not ready,
should we come another day?

523
00:36:16,670 --> 00:36:17,920
Today's the day.

524
00:36:18,490 --> 00:36:19,660
Be more confident.

525
00:36:20,860 --> 00:36:21,860
Come on.

526
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,240
Hey, P'Arthit.

527
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,380
You scared the hell out of me.

528
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:40,730
What should we do?

529
00:36:41,890 --> 00:36:43,820
Phoon, now's the moment.

530
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:46,070
Put it down there. He'll see it.

531
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:48,670
He'll take it to P'Fah himself. Go.

532
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:50,720
Right now.

533
00:36:50,830 --> 00:36:51,590
Damn it.

534
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,170
P'Fah has hundreds of friends.

535
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:55,460
Why does it have to be
this idiot who needs to pee?

536
00:36:56,650 --> 00:36:57,970
Then it has to be this idiot.

537
00:36:58,650 --> 00:36:59,650
- On me.
- Huh?

538
00:37:03,830 --> 00:37:04,830
Be careful, okay?

539
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:08,950
- North, stop messing around. Hurry up.
- Relax.

540
00:37:12,850 --> 00:37:14,510
Why don't you rappel down next time?

541
00:38:09,620 --> 00:38:11,090
To: Tonfah.

542
00:38:14,050 --> 00:38:15,730
Do you think I'm a delivery rider or what?

543
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,400
Hey!

544
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:34,280
- What?!
- He just ate it.

545
00:38:37,570 --> 00:38:38,630
What's wrong with him?

546
00:38:40,110 --> 00:38:41,110
How come?

547
00:38:41,210 --> 00:38:42,220
It's okay.

548
00:38:44,390 --> 00:38:45,390
It's okay, man.

549
00:38:46,100 --> 00:38:47,160
It's just a snack.

550
00:38:47,790 --> 00:38:49,930
But I think the letter should reach him.

551
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,280
Yeah.

552
00:38:51,660 --> 00:38:52,190
I guess.

553
00:38:52,270 --> 00:38:53,270
Wait

554
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,490
I don't know, what if he ate the letter too?

555
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:57,120
Who the hell eats letters, North?

556
00:38:57,870 --> 00:38:59,380
His name's Arthit, right?

557
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:01,160
Yeah, P'Fah's friend.

558
00:39:01,430 --> 00:39:02,620
Bad attitude.

559
00:39:03,210 --> 00:39:05,650
If he were nice, would he eat
someone else's stuff like that?

560
00:39:14,530 --> 00:39:15,530
Fah.

561
00:39:15,870 --> 00:39:16,910
Someone left this for you.

562
00:39:20,850 --> 00:39:22,960
- Is it good?
- Yeah, it's good.

563
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:27,770
How many pieces is this today already?
You've got a lot of admirers lately.

564
00:39:29,050 --> 00:39:30,050
Yeah.

565
00:39:32,330 --> 00:39:33,330
Open it.

566
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:36,340
I thought you ate it all.

567
00:39:36,610 --> 00:39:37,630
There's more.

568
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,380
Hey, there's milk left.

569
00:39:57,680 --> 00:39:58,850
I really like you so much.

570
00:40:00,470 --> 00:40:01,690
What are you smiling about?

571
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:04,920
Nothing.

572
00:40:05,390 --> 00:40:06,390
Cute.

573
00:40:26,570 --> 00:40:28,070
Is it worked?

574
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:38,210
Speak of the devil.

575
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,590
We'll begin the next
mission starting tomorrow.

576
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:50,410
I'd like to inform you that I've
found a delivery person for you.

577
00:40:50,820 --> 00:40:54,270
Bobby is willing to deliver for you every
morning in exchange for one can of cola.

578
00:40:54,750 --> 00:41:01,480
I guarantee that P'Fah will never
be able to trace it back to you. Over.

579
00:41:06,450 --> 00:41:08,250
Copy that. Out!

580
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,730
Why chocolate milk anyway?

581
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,480
Because I like it.

582
00:41:25,790 --> 00:41:26,860
And you bought just one?

583
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:31,610
- I could've bought them all.
- Ooh, big spender.

584
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,280
Hey!

585
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:42,250
That one's Bobby's.

586
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,400
Who's Bobby?

587
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:46,970
Cupid.

588
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:48,810
I mean Bobby.

589
00:41:48,970 --> 00:41:51,220
He's a friend of my cousin.

590
00:41:51,450 --> 00:41:52,830
Some distant relative, and...

591
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:55,180
Huh?

592
00:41:57,370 --> 00:41:59,670
Well, Bobby is...

593
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:06,040
Just one is fine.

594
00:42:07,330 --> 00:42:09,400
One is enough to fill P'Arthit anyway.

595
00:42:11,410 --> 00:42:12,626
Better than throwing it away.

596
00:42:12,650 --> 00:42:13,650
Yeah.

597
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:19,910
So about the letter...

598
00:42:20,060 --> 00:42:21,780
Do you know what you're going to write yet?

599
00:42:22,990 --> 00:42:24,120
Hmm.

600
00:42:26,670 --> 00:42:27,790
I honestly have no idea yet.

601
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:37,690
Don't forget, man. Your first letter has to
make a grand debut. So he'll remember you.

602
00:42:39,380 --> 00:42:40,470
Enough already.

603
00:42:41,740 --> 00:42:43,140
Why make such a big deal out of it?

604
00:42:44,890 --> 00:42:47,180
So P'Fah will be impressed.

605
00:42:54,410 --> 00:42:55,620
I'll give it a try.

606
00:42:59,470 --> 00:43:01,410
How dare you take my snacks out?

607
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:08,930
Where's the letter?

608
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:11,130
Here. I'm about to write it.

609
00:43:20,290 --> 00:43:22,520
Hurry up. I've got class, you know.

610
00:43:27,190 --> 00:43:28,930
What do you think of my handwriting?

611
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:33,740
- Looks natural?
- Hey, it works. Pretty convincing.

612
00:43:34,180 --> 00:43:35,760
You're good at forging handwriting too.

613
00:43:36,860 --> 00:43:37,940
Not weird, right?

614
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:39,610
Heh. Perfect.

615
00:43:46,590 --> 00:43:47,670
Give this to Bobby too.

616
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,360
Roger that.

617
00:43:49,650 --> 00:43:50,650
Count on me.

618
00:43:51,580 --> 00:43:52,580
Hey.

619
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:54,280
See you.

620
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:16,640
P'Fah.

621
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:21,790
Um… someone asked me to give this to you.

622
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:23,640
Yes.

623
00:44:43,770 --> 00:44:44,770
Thank you.

624
00:45:11,850 --> 00:45:15,680
This morning, the weather is nice.
The sky is clear.

625
00:45:16,040 --> 00:45:17,760
The sun isn't too harsh.

626
00:45:18,370 --> 00:45:20,420
It's a good start to the day.

627
00:45:20,530 --> 00:45:23,160
I hope you'll be happy all day long.

628
00:45:41,670 --> 00:45:44,980
That Bobby guy delivered
it straight to P'Fah himself.

629
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:47,610
So what did P'Fah say?

630
00:45:48,380 --> 00:45:49,380
He didn't say anything.

631
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:52,880
Okay.

632
00:45:53,130 --> 00:45:55,540
Hey, it's fine. You're just getting started.

633
00:45:55,660 --> 00:45:56,230
Yeah.

634
00:45:56,290 --> 00:45:58,670
Don't you realize how many
people send him stuff every day?

635
00:45:59,210 --> 00:46:02,130
True. This kind of thing takes consistency.

636
00:46:02,310 --> 00:46:04,446
If you keep sending them,
you'll win him over eventually.

637
00:46:04,470 --> 00:46:05,470
Exactly.

638
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:06,640
But...

639
00:46:07,060 --> 00:46:09,720
Honestly, I don't want
to compete with anyone.

640
00:46:11,940 --> 00:46:14,500
I just want to be by
P'Fah's side, in any way.

641
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:17,910
So many people like him anyway.

642
00:46:18,510 --> 00:46:20,490
I don't think it has to be me.

643
00:46:21,630 --> 00:46:25,620
- But it's impossible not to nope, right?
- Hope.

644
00:46:26,370 --> 00:46:27,370
Well…

645
00:46:27,990 --> 00:46:29,100
Just a little.

646
00:46:29,300 --> 00:46:31,340
Only a little, though.

647
00:46:32,460 --> 00:46:34,210
Yeah, so...

648
00:46:34,490 --> 00:46:36,040
Why send letters anyway?

649
00:46:36,670 --> 00:46:39,910
- Honestly, wouldn't adding him on LINE be easier?
- Come on.

650
00:46:40,060 --> 00:46:42,750
I'd probably get blocked right away.

651
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:47,350
Maew likes writing letters,
so he's using the way he likes.

652
00:46:47,610 --> 00:46:49,870
To express his feelings
to someone he likes.

653
00:46:50,130 --> 00:46:51,300
That feels best.

654
00:46:51,980 --> 00:46:53,820
Yeah, I mean...

655
00:46:54,170 --> 00:46:55,470
Writing letters…

656
00:46:56,070 --> 00:46:58,840
It's like reflecting on your own feelings.

657
00:46:59,530 --> 00:47:00,980
Besides getting to...

658
00:47:01,250 --> 00:47:02,970
Write to the person you love,

659
00:47:03,290 --> 00:47:04,730
You also get to understand yourself.

660
00:47:04,830 --> 00:47:07,610
Even if he doesn't reply to your letters.

661
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:10,230
Even if P'Tonfah doesn't reply,

662
00:47:10,500 --> 00:47:12,580
At least he'll know that.

663
00:47:12,750 --> 00:47:14,160
Someone out there likes him.

664
00:47:14,490 --> 00:47:15,490
Yeah.

665
00:47:15,960 --> 00:47:16,960
True.

666
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:19,010
That's better than liking
someone for nothing.

667
00:47:19,630 --> 00:47:21,430
What do you mean,
liking someone for nothing?

668
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,190
Liking them and keeping it to yourself.

669
00:47:24,450 --> 00:47:29,520
If you love someone and they don't
even know, what's the point in the end?

670
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:35,360
For me, meant well only has meaning
when it actually reaches someone.

671
00:47:35,780 --> 00:47:38,010
Hey, hey. Ow.

672
00:47:42,300 --> 00:47:45,180
So when you realized you liked P'Jo,

673
00:47:45,360 --> 00:47:46,470
What did you do?

674
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:48,650
I told him straight up.

675
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:50,720
And I even gave him my gear.

676
00:47:52,140 --> 00:47:54,930
- He gave him his gear before they were even dating.
- Of course.

677
00:47:55,020 --> 00:47:56,880
If I like him, why would I hold back?

678
00:47:57,720 --> 00:47:59,150
I don't think I could do that.

679
00:47:59,690 --> 00:48:03,180
You don't have to be like
me. What you're doing is fine.

680
00:48:04,030 --> 00:48:05,550
Don't overthink it yet.

681
00:48:05,750 --> 00:48:07,850
Wait and see how P'Tonfah reacts first.

682
00:48:08,170 --> 00:48:12,630
If he really isn't okay with
it, then you can step back.

683
00:48:12,980 --> 00:48:14,510
Huh? Step back?

684
00:48:14,650 --> 00:48:16,840
Hey, just back off like that?

685
00:48:17,580 --> 00:48:19,290
- You just started.
- True.

686
00:48:20,030 --> 00:48:24,170
I think you should keep sending letters
like this and see how he responds first.

687
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:28,520
But in the end, you have to let him know
that you're Typhoon who likes him.

688
00:48:28,730 --> 00:48:30,170
Not just the kid next door.

689
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:32,600
Come on. You've got this.

690
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:37,850
Don't overthink it, Maew.

691
00:48:38,860 --> 00:48:39,860
Is it good?

692
00:48:40,170 --> 00:48:44,350
With them around, even
heavy things feel lighter.

693
00:48:45,580 --> 00:48:47,900
I felt like I'd been given a
special blessing by you, Fun.

694
00:48:48,430 --> 00:48:49,680
Since having friends,

695
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:52,620
I no longer felt abandoned.

696
00:48:53,350 --> 00:48:54,910
Don't worry, Fun.

697
00:48:55,370 --> 00:48:57,050
I'm stronger now.

698
00:48:57,380 --> 00:49:00,360
I eat more, sleep more,

699
00:49:00,580 --> 00:49:02,360
Smile and laugh,

700
00:49:02,680 --> 00:49:04,200
And much happier.

701
00:49:04,890 --> 00:49:09,270
And most importantly, I finally had
the courage to follow my own feelings.

702
00:49:09,630 --> 00:49:12,730
From now on, it's up to P'Fah.

703
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:54,120
The weather is nice this morning.

704
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:58,000
The sky is clear, and
the sun isn't too hot.

705
00:49:58,660 --> 00:50:00,690
It's a good way to start the day.

706
00:50:00,870 --> 00:50:03,590
I hope you'll be happy all day.

707
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:13,400
Mm.

708
00:50:17,610 --> 00:50:19,760
I don't think P'Fah likes it.

709
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:23,930
I won't tease you then.

710
00:50:24,690 --> 00:50:26,670
I'm going.

711
00:50:35,100 --> 00:50:37,190
Hello? Yes, yes.

712
00:50:38,080 --> 00:50:39,080
Hurry up, hurry.

713
00:50:42,010 --> 00:50:43,780
Let's go, go.

714
00:51:11,040 --> 00:51:13,560
P'Fah, enjoy your meal.

715
00:51:14,200 --> 00:51:15,230
Thank you.

716
00:51:21,420 --> 00:51:23,050
You seem more okay than I expected.

717
00:51:23,600 --> 00:51:24,600
How so?

718
00:51:27,770 --> 00:51:29,890
I thought you were
going to back off already.

719
00:51:30,270 --> 00:51:31,440
P'Fah didn't reply.

720
00:51:31,820 --> 00:51:33,340
And there are other competitors too.

721
00:51:35,200 --> 00:51:38,310
It's not that bad, even
though I want to talk to him.

722
00:51:39,120 --> 00:51:42,140
If this is all it gets to
be, then this is all it is.

723
00:51:45,710 --> 00:51:48,140
Do you remember what you told me, North?

724
00:51:48,750 --> 00:51:51,040
At least it reached him.

725
00:51:52,170 --> 00:51:53,190
My feelings.

726
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,260
I'm glad you're okay.

727
00:52:00,290 --> 00:52:01,900
You've really grown up, Maew.

728
00:52:46,780 --> 00:52:50,340
Jo, look at Fah. He's being possessive.

729
00:53:02,590 --> 00:53:05,150
I guess you haven't eaten breakfast yet.

730
00:53:05,520 --> 00:53:09,130
You might be wondering why I often give
you tuna sandwiches and chocolate milk.

731
00:53:09,530 --> 00:53:11,690
It's not because I don't
know what else to give you.

732
00:53:12,270 --> 00:53:14,090
I just think they taste good.

733
00:53:51,700 --> 00:53:52,700
Hey.

734
00:53:53,190 --> 00:53:54,260
What is it?

735
00:53:55,650 --> 00:53:56,650
What's this?

736
00:53:56,970 --> 00:53:58,120
Just open it.

737
00:54:06,020 --> 00:54:08,500
Chocolate milk and
sandwiches really are delicious.

738
00:54:08,870 --> 00:54:10,420
Make sure you finish them.

739
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:17,470
Caught you.

740
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,200
So, do you like him?

741
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:21,946
Not to the point of liking him yet.

742
00:54:21,970 --> 00:54:23,410
I just want to get to know him more.

743
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:25,610
I feel like I could float right now.

744
00:54:25,700 --> 00:54:28,940
Does he like you, or
the person in the letters?

745
00:54:29,530 --> 00:54:32,400
He keeps trying to draw a line between us.

746
00:54:32,820 --> 00:54:34,760
But I've never crossed that line.

747
00:54:34,990 --> 00:54:37,210
Look at this. P'Fah is
totally flirting with you.

748
00:54:37,370 --> 00:54:39,460
So what about the person
who sent the letters?

749
00:54:39,610 --> 00:54:42,060
I think he's pretty cute.

750
00:54:42,340 --> 00:54:43,980
Happy birthday.

751
00:54:44,180 --> 00:54:45,290
Thank you.

752
00:54:45,690 --> 00:54:47,510
Don't you want to know who he is?
